<HL>
   Business Brief -- Alcan Aluminium Ltd.:
   Four Can-Recycling Firms
   Are Acquired by Company
</HL>
<DATE>
07/12/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C12
</SO>
<CO>
   AL
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Alcan Aluminium Ltd. said it acquired four aluminum
beverage can collection and processing concerns.
   Alcan said it acquired Reliable Recycling Inc. and the
assets of UBC Recycling Inc., both based in Brampton, a
Toronto suburb. Alcan said it acquired the assets of R.
Johnson Management Services Ltd. and Camco Recycling Services
Ltd., both based in Lachine, a Montreal suburb. Terms weren't
disclosed.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Alcan, based in Montreal, said the four acquisitions,
combined with a Vancouver, British Columbia, recycling
concern acquired earlier this year, give it an annual
collection and processing capacity of two billion aluminum
beverage cans a year.
</TEXT>
